A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO STATE BOATING FACILITIES.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that the division of
2 boating and ocean recreation of the department of land and
3 natural resources is tasked with thirteen statutory mandates
4 primarily relating to the operation and management of state
5 small boat harbors and the administration of the ocean
6 recreation program. However, the legislature recognizes that,
7 due to statutory limitations, the division has been unable to
8 meet its statutory mandate of administering the ocean recreation
9 management program and has disproportionately devoted almost all
10 of its staff and resources to the operation and management of
11 the sixteen state small boat harbors, which include more than
12 two thousand slips and numerous boat launch ramp facilities
13 throughout the State, leaving very few resources available for
14 major statutory responsibilities of regulating and managing
15 ocean recreation.
16 The legislature notes that the division has historically
17 been severely underfunded, understaffed, and unable to meet its
2026-2518 SB2367 CDl SMA.docx
