C.D. 1
1 statutory mandates to manage and maintain the sixteen small boat
2 harbors. Due to inflation and increased construction costs, the
3 division had approximately $1,100,000,000 in deferred
4 maintenance costs as of 2024. With an annual operational budget
5 of roughly $30,000,000, the division is unable to address this
6 deferred maintenance backlog, leaving facilities in disrepair
7 while awaiting capital improvement project funding from the
8 legislature.
9 The legislature further finds that it is nearly impossible
10 to quantify ocean recreation management program underfunding
11 because ocean recreation activities are widespread throughout
12 the ocean waters of the State. Furthermore, the division has
13 not been able to adequately administer the ocean recreation
14 management program for the reasons stated, resulting in
15 increased user conflicts, ocean safety concerns, and illegal
16 commercial ocean activities.
17 The legislature also finds that the Ala Wai small boat
18 harbor is the "gateway to Waikiki". The harbor has significant
19 potential to provide a positive and memorable welcome to
20 residents and visitors as they enter Waikiki and to be a
21 community space for gatherings and recreational activities, as
2026-2518 SB2367 CDl SMA.docx
