1 envisioned by decades of community planning and summarized most
2 recently in the 2022 University of Hawaii Community Design
3 Center Ala Wai Small Boat Harbor Vision Report (2022 UH Report).
4 Engaging in alternative management options for state small boat
5 harbors, namely public-private partnerships for management of
6 small boat harbor operations, while preserving the jobs of
7 public employees working in the area, could improve small boat
8 harbor conditions, create a more inviting atmosphere for all
9 users, and'enable the division to better devote its time and
10 resources to the administration of the ocean recreation
11 management program.
12 However, the legislature also finds that it is important to
13 ensure safe and meaningful public access and parking for
14 residents and visitors heading to the shoreline for relaxation
15 and recreation, including to a boat ramp. It is likewise
16 critical to ensure safe and comfortable multimodal access across
17 the shoreline between Ala Moana beach park and Waikiki beach,
18 extending the lei of parks, and creating a place appropriate and
19 aesthetically appropriate gateway to Waikiki, as envisioned by
20 the 2022 UH Report.
