1 The legislature further finds that a prime example of a
2 state-owned harbor under private management is the Kewalo basin
3 harbor under the Hawaii community development authority, which
4 is leased to Howard Hughes Holdings, Inc., and managed by Almar
5 Marinas. The public-private partnership at Kewalo basin harbor
6 has resulted in timely repairs and maintenance, as well as a
7 regular staff presence to monitor harbor activities and assist
8 users, enhancing public access to a more enjoyable space.
9 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to;
10 (1) Allow the board of land and natural resources to lease
11 the management of the remaining portion of Ala Wai
12 small boat harbor, including fast lands and submerged
13 lands within its boundaries, by public auction,
14 request for proposals, or direct negotiation for
15 private development, management, and operation;
16 provided that public employees at Ala Wai small boat
17 harbor are retained; and
18 (2) Develop and implement a project to improve those
19 portions of Ala Wai small boat harbor that provide for
20 public space and access to the shoreline, including
21 public parking and multimodal access, extending the
