1 "Parcel A" and the areas immediately along the length of
2 Holomoana street from Ala Moana boulevard to Kahanamoku street,
3 including the lot known as "Parcel D" and the Ala Moana Bowls
4 parking lot, as identified in the 2022 UH Report. The project
5 shall ensure meaningful public parking within and nearest to the
6 Ala Moana Bowls parking lot and provide for cohesive, safe, and
7 comfortable multimodal access along a promenade connecting Ala
8 Moana beach park to Waikiki beach, extending the lei of parks
9 and creating a place- and aesthetically-appropriate gateway to
10 Waikiki, as envisioned by the 2022 UH Report.
11 SECTION 6. All employees of the division of boating and
12 ocean recreation of the department of land and natural resources
13 who occupy civil service positions and whose functions are
14 replaced as a result of this Act shall retain their civil
15 service status, whether permanent or temporary. Employees shall
16 be reassigned within the division of boating and ocean
17 recreation without loss of salary, seniority (except as
18 prescribed by applicable collective bargaining agreements),
19 retention points, prior service credit, any vacation and sick
20 leave credits previously earned, and other rights, benefits, and
21 privileges, in accordance with state personnel laws; provided
